		<table width="90%" bgcolor="" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-left-width:1; border-right-width: 1; border-top-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-top-width: 1; border-bottom-width: 1" bordercolor="#FFFFFF" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">  
		<tr>
			<td align="left" valign="top" background="/images/necrotableheader2.gif">
				<font width="100%" face="verdana" size="1" color=white><b>Soloing Level 12-30-- Necromancers</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#ffebdc">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="verdana" size="1" color=white>
				written by <b>fracas</b> on <b>5/28/2003 11:49:33 AM</b>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr bgcolor="#37437B">
			<td align="left" valign="top" valign="top">
				<font face="verdana" size="1" color=white><blockquote><br>
				From around level 12-13 start soloing Orcs along the orc highway in Oasis of Marr.  Set up shop around the bend in the lake away from other groups (or you WILL get trained) and park your pet near the water. Then just run out and pull a wandering orc to your pet. Pull blues and evens and even yellows -- avoid the reds till around 14-15.  The fear-pathing will cause the orc to wander along the shore and not back out into "orc-traffic".<br>At around level 16, Paludal Caverns is by far the best experience zone in the game.  Start by soloing Phlarg fiends along the ramp to the right as you zone in from Shadowhaven.  As you solo look for a group periodically. Soloing the Phlargs is very easy and nets at least a blue bub per kill. The key is to get in a group in one of the bandit camps -- a good group will help you gain 2-3 levels in one night. Yah, no s**t.  At around 24 the Phlargs will start becoming light blue, but the bandit camps will still yield pretty good xp.  As I recall, I did not fear kite the fiends -- just tanked em and healed my pet. Keep Cure Disease handy as the fiends hit you with a nasty Crud disease similar to the mummy rot in OoM.<br>At 24-25 head to Lake of Ill Omen.  Use the PoK book to Firiona Vie and GATHER SHADOWS. The FV guards wandering the tunnels are were red to me at 25+ and KOS.<br>Run straight from the book in FV til the tunnel ends at a "T" ( a funny sand triangle will be right in front of you ) and hang a left. Upon leaving the tunnel, hang a left and follow the zone wall to the river/Loio zone line. Of course avoid those frigging Drachs. Snickety-snickety-snick. That sound still makes me break into a sweat.  Bind at the zone line ( in LOIO, for God's sake )<br>and then set up shop along the lake between the Sarnak Fort front door and Back door.  Park your pet and watch which direction he "points" and run out and grab the mob -- Sabertooth Grimalkins (resistant, fight to death, but good xp) Skellies (fight to finish, but drop good pet weapons), Sarnaks, and Goblins are the main fare.  Dark Blue and Even cons thru about 28-29, some light blue after that. About a blue bub per kill.  The fear-pathing here is awesome. Pull with Engulfing Darkness, sic pet about 50 yards from shore, fear.  The mob will wander down to the shore, and hang a left on the beach. Again, like OoM, out of the way of other mob traffic.  Keep pet healed and buffed. Throw a few DoTs and Voila' -- dead mob.  About 1-3 plat per kill too.<br>If a wandering mob should jump your ass while your pet is occupied, just Feign Death ( your best spell in the book ), and lay low. When your pet has finished off the mob he is killing he will run grab the new mob. Just stand up and repeat the process.  Note:  I kept KEI up at all times -- when it faded I gated to bind point and got my arse to the nexus for a fresh one.  It is possible to solo without KEI, but with it you can practically chain pull for your pet.  With KEI, no need for Allure of Death or Siphon Life.  Just Engulf Dkness, Fear, Heart Flutter or Heat Blood, and throw in a few Shock of Poisons.<br>I was rarely ever hit by a mob.  Keep in mind -- park yourself barely within spell range of the fear-kite path.  When the mob aggros you it will give you plenty of time to get off another Fear.<br>I leveled from 24 to 30 here in three days, and netted about 150 plat -- enough for my level 29 spells.<br><br>Enjoy!<br><br>Soulmonger<br>30 Necromancer<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br>
			</td>
		</tr>
